for decades but they've been unsuccessful.

01:06:15.835 --> 01:06:20.373
Then there are the white witches or Wiccans
who commune in nature in the healing spirit...

01:06:20.473 --> 01:06:23.592
...and who have a strict law
that forbids harming others.

01:06:23.692 --> 01:06:27.246
Every city and rural village today has
pockets of both black and white witches...

01:06:27.346 --> 01:06:29.355
...who practice the ancient rites.

01:07:00.912 --> 01:07:06.090
I invoke and call upon thee,
mighty mother of us all.

01:07:06.651 --> 01:07:10.458
I invoke thee to descend upon the body...

01:07:10.558 --> 01:07:14.098
...of this thy servant and priestess.

01:07:15.593 --> 01:07:18.164
Of the mother darksome and divine...

01:07:18.264 --> 01:07:20.759
...here I charge you in this sign.

01:07:23.435 --> 01:07:26.178
Listen to the words of the great mother.

01:07:29.141 --> 01:07:32.478
She, who of old,
who was also called Artemis...

01:07:32.778 --> 01:07:35.586
...Aphrodite, Ceridwyn...

01:07:35.686 --> 01:07:38.150
...Diana, Isis...

01:07:38.250 --> 01:07:41.158
...and by many other names.

01:07:43.690 --> 01:07:46.292
Whenever ye have need of anything...

01:07:46.392 --> 01:07:49.853
...then ye shall assemble
in some secret place...

01:07:49.953 --> 01:07:51.596
...and adore me...

01:07:51.696 --> 01:07:53.978
...who am queen of all witches.

01:07:54.533 --> 01:07:56.831
There shall ye assemble...

01:07:56.931 --> 01:07:59.877
...ye who are fain to learn all sorcery.

01:08:00.672 --> 01:08:05.127
Behold all acts of love
and pleasure are my rituals.

01:08:05.811 --> 01:08:08.962
Behold I have been with thee
from the beginning...

01:08:09.062 --> 01:08:13.358
...and I am that which is attained
at the end of desire.

01:08:35.941 --> 01:08:37.581
Arise.

01:09:18.649 --> 01:09:22.529
You're looking a little tense tonight,
love. What's the matter?

01:09:23.455 --> 01:09:27.560
Nothing, just my usual
roller coaster love life.

01:09:27.660 --> 01:09:29.595
Well, have a drink and relax.

01:09:29.694 --> 01:09:33.618
Nothing's that dire, at least not for you.

01:09:33.732 --> 01:09:37.408
It's an entirely different story
for your victims.

01:09:39.371 --> 01:09:40.406
What victims?

01:09:40.506 --> 01:09:44.176
There's no need to play
Miss Innocent with me, dearie.

01:09:44.277 --> 01:09:46.350
Please, don't touch me.

01:09:52.417 --> 01:09:56.622
- Bright blessings, Barbara.
- Merry meet, Elaine. How's it going?

01:09:56.722 --> 01:10:00.292
- I'm back in the dating pool again.
- What happened?

01:10:00.392 --> 01:10:04.629
I thought you were crazy about that new
guy you were seeing, the married man.

01:10:04.729 --> 01:10:06.898
No, I broke it off.

01:10:06.998 --> 01:10:10.508
He just became really obsessive, morose...

01:10:11.202 --> 01:10:14.075
...and his aura became really murky.

01:10:14.506 --> 01:10:17.677
He didn't even wanna make love anymore.

01:10:17.777 --> 01:10:21.797
He became just like a woman,
crying at every little thing.

01:10:22.347 --> 01:10:24.350
There was no polarity.

01:10:24.950 --> 01:10:28.674
But I should have known. He's a Pisces.

01:10:59.484 --> 01:11:01.125
Richard.

01:11:03.621 --> 01:11:07.093
I thought I told you never to
interrupt me when I'm working.

01:11:07.193 --> 01:11:08.733
What do you want?

01:11:09.595 --> 01:11:13.105
I just wanted to let you know
that I'm going to bed and I'm taking a pill.

01:11:32.050 --> 01:11:34.052
Are you coming to bed?

01:11:34.152 --> 01:11:35.660
No.

01:11:41.159 --> 01:11:43.169
I have some more work to do.

01:11:46.364 --> 01:11:49.074
All right, see you tomorrow, then.

01:13:23.928 --> 01:13:26.465
Sergeant Griff Meadows
of the Police Department.

01:13:26.565 --> 01:13:29.840
- I'd like to ask you a few questions.
- Okay.

01:13:39.510 --> 01:13:41.724
Does this look familiar to you?

01:13:46.291 --> 01:13:48.219
It's a witch bottle.

01:13:48.319 --> 01:13:50.422
Do you have any idea who could have made it?

01:13:50.522 --> 01:13:53.363
No. No, I don't.

01:13:55.493 --> 01:13:57.863
Ever seen any of these in here before?

01:13:57.963 --> 01:14:00.066
Yeah, we have some witch bottles.

01:14:00.166 --> 01:14:01.973
I'll show you one.

01:14:08.940 --> 01:14:10.781
Here's one.

01:14:13.478 --> 01:14:15.381
How common are these bottles?

01:14:15.481 --> 01:14:20.419
I've never seen 'em in here before
until a girl started supplying 'em to us.

01:14:20.752 --> 01:14:22.827
Who is this girl?

01:14:23.888 --> 01:14:27.331
Her name is Elaine, Elaine Parks.

01:14:54.051 --> 01:14:55.859
Who is it?

01:14:56.621 --> 01:14:59.097
Sergeant Meadows, Police Department.

01:15:05.062 --> 01:15:07.399
Sorry to bother you, ma'am,
but I'm investigating a case...

01:15:07.499 --> 01:15:10.169
...and I just wanted to ask you
a few questions.

01:15:10.269 --> 01:15:11.973
About what?

01:15:12.073 --> 01:15:14.506
Well, it's a potential homicide case.

01:15:14.606 --> 01:15:16.542
Just a routine check.

01:15:16.642 --> 01:15:18.878
I thought you might be able to help us.

01:15:20.278 --> 01:15:22.119
Of course.

01:15:23.514 --> 01:15:26.390
Please come in, Sergeant.

01:15:32.623 --> 01:15:34.973
So you say there was a homicide.

01:15:35.593 --> 01:15:37.467
How horrible.

01:15:37.762 --> 01:15:42.000
- Who was killed?
- A man named Wayne Peters.

01:15:42.100 --> 01:15:44.622
- Did you know Wayne Peters?
- No.

01:15:48.205 --> 01:15:51.076
Here's a picture of him.
Ever seen him before?

01:15:51.176 --> 01:15:54.313
No. I guess I can't help you, Sergeant.

01:15:54.413 --> 01:15:57.821
- Good bye.
- Ms. Parks, wait.

01:16:04.655 --> 01:16:07.632
Have you ever seen anything like this before?

01:16:07.859 --> 01:16:11.497
It's a magic bottle. I made it myself.

01:16:12.302 --> 01:16:15.000
Have you ever seen one containing urine?

01:16:15.450 --> 01:16:16.841
Urine?

01:16:17.902 --> 01:16:19.443
No.

01:16:29.747 --> 01:16:32.942
We found this bottle containing urine...

01:16:33.042 --> 01:16:35.100
...and a used tampon...

01:16:35.200 --> 01:16:37.214
...on the grave of Wayne Peters.

01:16:39.158 --> 01:16:42.200
Will you excuse me for a moment, Sergeant?

01:16:48.366 --> 01:16:51.102
Ms. Parks, are you a witch?

01:16:51.202 --> 01:16:54.740
Yes, I am. Is there a law against that?

01:16:54.840 --> 01:16:58.577
I guess not, not unless
you do something wrong.

01:16:58.677 --> 01:17:01.379
Do you think that being
a witch makes me evil...

01:17:01.479 --> 01:17:03.498
...capable of murder even?

01:17:03.598 --> 01:17:06.352
No, I wasn't trying to imply...

01:17:06.452 --> 01:17:08.329
Sergeant Meadows...

01:17:08.929 --> 01:17:12.209
...do you know
what it's like to really suffer?

01:17:12.608 --> 01:17:16.814
You have to fight and fight
until you're too exhausted to go on.

01:17:17.263 --> 01:17:20.766
Witchcraft is my religion, Sergeant.

01:17:20.866 --> 01:17:25.003
And this religion, which is older
than your Christianity...

01:17:25.103 --> 01:17:27.111
...saved my life.

01:17:40.885 --> 01:17:42.594
Ms. Parks...

01:17:43.272 --> 01:17:45.479
...I'm sorry if I've offended you.

01:17:47.024 --> 01:17:48.866
I didn't realize.

01:17:51.896 --> 01:17:54.430
That's all right, Sergeant...

01:17:55.599 --> 01:17:57.251
...Meadow.

01:18:00.205 --> 01:18:02.393
You can call me Griff.

01:18:03.641 --> 01:18:05.282
Griff?

01:18:07.646 --> 01:18:10.457
I know I've seen you before.

01:18:11.882 --> 01:18:14.091
I just don't know where.

01:18:14.919 --> 01:18:16.922
I have that same feeling.

01:18:17.822 --> 01:18:19.663
I know.

01:18:23.060 --> 01:18:25.303
You're the man in the cards.

01:18:26.731 --> 01:18:28.605
You're my fate.

01:18:29.300 --> 01:18:31.704
What do you mean, I'm your fate?

01:18:32.304 --> 01:18:34.646
I did a Celtic cross reading.

01:18:35.840 --> 01:18:38.970
For my future card I got knight of wands.

01:18:40.778 --> 01:18:44.442
Always felt that if that card
showed up in a future reading...

01:18:44.867 --> 01:18:47.411
...soon meet the man that I'm going to marry.

01:18:48.491 --> 01:18:51.293
But the man that I marry has to love animals.

01:18:52.724 --> 01:18:54.993
Do you like animals, Griff?

01:18:55.093 --> 01:18:58.067
Why yes, I love animals.

01:18:58.167 --> 01:19:01.320
In fact, a friend of mine has
a couple horses I'm very fond of.

01:19:02.400 --> 01:19:05.000
You know, tomorrow is my day off...

01:19:05.100 --> 01:19:06.973
...and it's supposed to be quite nice out.

01:19:08.173 --> 01:19:11.244
Maybe I'll get away from the city
and do some riding.

01:19:12.344 --> 01:19:15.185
Do you like to ride, Elaine?

01:20:09.710 --> 01:20:11.339
Patchouli...

01:20:11.975 --> 01:20:13.828
...you're such a sweetheart.

01:20:23.180 --> 01:20:25.022
How's my girl?

01:20:25.316 --> 01:20:27.084
Am I your girl?

01:20:27.184 --> 01:20:29.060
For today you are.

01:20:30.187 --> 01:20:33.697
You're my girl and there's nobody
around to tell me otherwise.

01:20:35.259 --> 01:20:37.140
Except me.

01:20:37.395 --> 01:20:39.664
And what's that supposed to mean?

01:20:40.952 --> 01:20:42.606
Nothing.

01:20:43.114 --> 01:20:44.979
Kiss me.

01:20:55.880 --> 01:20:57.749
What's that sound?

01:20:58.249 --> 01:21:01.258
I don't know. Let's go see.

01:22:23.835 --> 01:22:27.178
Now is the time of the summer solstice.

01:22:27.717 --> 01:22:30.809
The strength of the Oak King is waning.

01:22:30.909 --> 01:22:34.012
And the Holly King stands ready
to challenge him...

01:22:34.112 --> 01:22:36.654
...for the hand of the Green Maiden.

01:22:38.582 --> 01:22:40.691
Let the battle begin.

01:22:46.057 --> 01:22:49.166
- Your season is over, old man.
- Never.

01:22:56.433 --> 01:22:59.471
- I will have her.
- Never have her.

01:23:00.371 --> 01:23:01.986
Never.

01:23:05.077 --> 01:23:07.292
Holly King, I name you the victor.

01:23:07.612 --> 01:23:10.954
- The Green Maiden is yours.
- M'lady.

01:23:12.484 --> 01:23:14.324
Come on.

01:23:19.623 --> 01:23:21.264
Elaine.

01:23:21.525 --> 01:23:24.496
- You know these people?
- Well, yes, in a way.

01:23:24.596 --> 01:23:29.067
All hail, fair lord and lady.
Welcome to our little gathering.

01:23:29.167 --> 01:23:30.966
All hail.

01:23:31.235 --> 01:23:34.657
We are the good people of
the renaissance and medieval players...

01:23:34.757 --> 01:23:37.142
...and we are celebrating the mid-summer.

01:23:37.242 --> 01:23:38.810
Won't you join us?

01:23:38.910 --> 01:23:41.818
To be sure, fair consort.

01:23:48.686 --> 01:23:52.629
- They are charming, are they not?
- Yes, quite charming.

01:23:52.990 --> 01:23:55.293
I see two people in love.

01:23:55.393 --> 01:23:57.562
This calls for a wedding.

01:23:57.862 --> 01:24:00.799
- A wedding?
- Yes, a mock wedding, if you will.

01:24:00.899 --> 01:24:04.373
To honor the Gods of love.

01:24:11.042 --> 01:24:15.310
<i>Love is a magical thing</i>

01:24:15.410 --> 01:24:19.378
<i>Love will make you feel
like a queen or a king</i>

01:24:19.778 --> 01:24:23.699
<i>Unicorns, rainbows, lucky charms</i>

01:24:23.799 --> 01:24:29.000
<i>Await you in your true love's arms</i>

01:24:30.889 --> 01:24:35.046
<i>Love is a magical thing</i>

01:24:35.146 --> 01:24:38.885
<i>Mystical, physical, alchemical</i>

01:24:39.235 --> 01:24:43.366
<i>We're pretending to be in love today</i>

01:24:43.616 --> 01:24:48.174
<i>But pretending is also real</i>

01:24:50.408 --> 01:24:53.887
<i>There's a lady in a castle</i>

01:24:53.987 --> 01:24:56.784
<i>She's sad and so forlorn</i>

01:24:57.174 --> 01:25:00.572
<i>When her troubadour returns and kisses her</i>

01:25:00.872 --> 01:25:04.155
<i>She's all smiles and laughter</i>

01:25:04.255 --> 01:25:07.221
<i>Lady, you're so beautiful</i>

01:25:07.321 --> 01:25:10.586
<i>Come lie with me and be my love</i>

01:25:10.686 --> 01:25:14.221
<i>I'd slay any dragon, endure any danger</i>

01:25:14.321 --> 01:25:18.872
<i>Just to have you near me</i>

01:25:19.505 --> 01:25:23.574
<i>Love is a magical thing</i>

01:25:23.894 --> 01:25:27.998
<i>Lucky lovers mate in the spring</i>

01:25:28.098 --> 01:25:32.007
<i>We sip from goblets full of joy</i>

01:25:32.227 --> 01:25:34.334
<i>But when love dies</i>

01:25:34.434 --> 01:25:40.002
<i>All life it does destroy</i>

01:26:04.857 --> 01:26:06.497
Okay.

01:27:28.422 --> 01:27:30.630
Now, ye are wed.

01:27:37.048 --> 01:27:40.553
I'm so happy for you, Elaine, he's adorable.

01:28:13.350 --> 01:28:15.053
<i>I'm not in love.</i>

01:28:15.153 --> 01:28:18.756
<i>It's not that I don't have sentiment,
it's just that love is soft.</i>

01:28:18.856 --> 01:28:20.925
<i>You need guts in this business.</i>

01:28:21.025 --> 01:28:25.662
<i>I've seen guys get shot to death because
they fell in love and got soft inside.</i>

01:28:25.762 --> 01:28:29.033
<i>I want an heir some day and then
I would need to have a wife...</i>

01:28:29.133 --> 01:28:31.436
<i>...but love is something else.</i>

01:28:31.536 --> 01:28:33.971
<i>A man can get destroyed by things like that.</i>

01:28:34.071 --> 01:28:36.441
<i>It's like he's not even a man anymore.</i>

01:28:36.541 --> 01:28:38.715
<i>I never wanna get that way.</i>

01:28:39.876 --> 01:28:42.180
<i>When you really love him...</i>

01:28:42.580 --> 01:28:46.851
<i>...it's like fireworks
and nothing else matters.</i>

01:28:46.951 --> 01:28:49.454
<i>You love all the little quirks about him.</i>

01:28:49.854 --> 01:28:52.262
<i>The way he slurps his cereal.</i>

01:28:52.623 --> 01:28:54.826
<i>The way his mouth is a little crooked.</i>

01:28:54.926 --> 01:28:58.997
<i>Those details about him
become your whole life.</i>

01:28:59.097 --> 01:29:03.400
<i>Something inside you
opens up like a flower...</i>

01:29:03.500 --> 01:29:06.971
<i>...and you realize that you
have more love to give...</i>

01:29:07.071 --> 01:29:10.040
<i>...than you ever thought was possible.</i>

01:29:10.340 --> 01:29:12.849
<i>'Cause the more you know him...</i>

01:29:13.944 --> 01:29:16.186
<i>...the more you love him.</i>

01:29:17.047 --> 01:29:21.019
<i>The more you get to know a woman,
the less you can feel about her.</i>

01:29:21.619 --> 01:29:23.721
<i>At first, she's this
incredible object of mystery...</i>

01:29:23.821 --> 01:29:26.658
<i>...who fulfills all you're wildest fantasies.</i>

01:29:27.658 --> 01:29:30.328
<i>Then she starts to reveal little flaws...</i>

01:29:30.728 --> 01:29:34.265
<i>...and after a while,
just gets pretty hard to care.</i>

01:29:35.165 --> 01:29:38.441
<i>Feminine ideal only exists in a man's mind.</i>

01:29:38.969 --> 01:29:41.235
<i>No woman could ever fulfill it.</i>

01:29:41.673 --> 01:29:45.217
<i>And sometimes,
when she tries to love you more...</i>

01:29:45.317 --> 01:29:47.285
<i>...give you more...</i>

01:29:47.885 --> 01:29:50.168
<i>...you feel like you're suffocating...</i>

01:29:50.268 --> 01:29:52.455
<i>...drowning in estrogen.</i>

01:29:53.417 --> 01:29:55.459
<i>The most awful feeling.</i>

01:30:03.460 --> 01:30:05.669
Dinner tonight, Griff?

01:30:07.230 --> 01:30:09.105
Can't tonight, Connie.

01:30:10.166 --> 01:30:12.008
Some other time.

01:30:17.441 --> 01:30:20.145
Hey, Griff, I got more information
on that Elaine Parks girl.

01:30:20.245 --> 01:30:22.380
You leave it on my desk.

01:30:22.480 --> 01:30:25.032
- Don't you wanna hear it?
- Steve...

01:30:25.132 --> 01:30:28.868
- Captain wants us to lay off the case.
- Are you serious?

01:30:29.268 --> 01:30:32.223
He says we have a policy
of leaving the witches alone.

01:30:32.323 --> 01:30:34.659
He says they've lived
in this town a long time...

01:30:34.759 --> 01:30:38.435
- ...and he doesn't like to mess with them.
- Even if they murder.

01:30:39.629 --> 01:30:42.483
He says he's satisfied that Wayne's
death was a heart attack.

01:30:43.233 --> 01:30:45.074
I think so too.

01:30:48.205 --> 01:30:50.642
Has everyone gone crazy around here?

01:30:50.742 --> 01:30:53.417
Let me at least tell you what I found.

01:30:58.849 --> 01:31:01.619
Now, Elaine used to run
an organic beauty store...

01:31:01.719 --> 01:31:03.754
...in Berkeley with her husband, Jerry.

01:31:03.854 --> 01:31:06.991
Two years later they were divorced
and Elaine moved to San Francisco...

01:31:07.091 --> 01:31:11.577
...to start dancing at a burlesque club
where she got involved with a witch coven.

01:31:20.103 --> 01:31:24.876
The coven broke up after police questioning
when some of it's members died mysteriously.

01:31:24.976 --> 01:31:29.714
Soon after, Elaine's ex-husband
died of a drug overdose...

01:31:29.814 --> 01:31:32.796
...shortly before he was planning to remarry.

01:31:33.418 --> 01:31:37.332
The police questioned Elaine but they
couldn't find enough to hold her.

01:31:37.755 --> 01:31:40.558
Well, if the San Francisco police
couldn't find anything...

01:31:40.658 --> 01:31:42.527
...what happened there
is none of our business.

01:31:42.627 --> 01:31:47.112
Are you serious? I'd say this woman
is a dangerous character...

01:31:47.212 --> 01:31:49.275
...and you better watch her.

01:31:49.375 --> 01:31:53.004
You mean because she's a witch?
That doesn't mean anything.

01:31:53.104 --> 01:31:57.306
No, her husband died of a drug
he'd never taken before.

01:31:57.406 --> 01:32:00.750
And did you ever find where
Wayne Peters got the devil's weed?

01:32:01.512 --> 01:32:03.881
I questioned Ms. Curtis about that.

01:32:03.981 --> 01:32:06.751
There was devil's weed
growing near his cabin.

01:32:06.851 --> 01:32:09.267
Apparently, he experimented often with drugs.

01:32:09.367 --> 01:32:11.589
Come on, Griff, can't you connect the dots?

01:32:11.689 --> 01:32:15.527
We have a possible murder here
and Elaine is our only suspect.

01:32:15.627 --> 01:32:18.146
I told you, we're laying off her.

01:32:18.246 --> 01:32:20.648
Because of orders
or because you're in love with her?

01:32:20.748 --> 01:32:23.917
Who says I'm in love with her?
Get the hell off my back.

01:32:28.939 --> 01:32:32.509
You're out of line, Griff, way out of line.

01:33:07.645 --> 01:33:09.285
Richard.

01:33:11.265 --> 01:33:12.905
Richard!

01:33:13.618 --> 01:33:15.185
Richard!

01:33:15.285 --> 01:33:16.926
Richard!

01:34:03.200 --> 01:34:05.370
Thank you for meeting me, Elaine.

01:34:05.470 --> 01:34:07.872
It's not good for me to be alone too much.

01:34:08.472 --> 01:34:12.983
- I know you're busy.
- Of course. I wanted to come.

01:34:15.178 --> 01:34:18.369
I can't help but blaming myself
for what happened.

01:34:18.950 --> 01:34:21.518
You can't blame yourself.

01:34:21.618 --> 01:34:25.029
You were a good wife to Richard.

01:34:25.889 --> 01:34:27.730
